entry.title: Revert "Accessibility: Implement Dictation keyboard improvements"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 68cbe69b809e3918c5ad275583ea285d6e8b6653.



Reason for revert: #gardener DictationKeyboardCombo/AccessibilityManagerDictationKeyboardImprovementsTest.DictationEnabled/0 flaky on go/linux-chromeos-chrome since https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chrome/builders/ci/linux-chromeos-chrome/34381/test-results



fake_speech_recognition_manager.cc(45): Failed

RunLoop::Run() timed out.

Unchecked runtime.lastError: Couldn't retrieve Pumpkin data."



Original change's description:

> Accessibility: Implement Dictation keyboard improvements

>

> This change implements improvements to Dictation's keyboard shortcuts

> (Search + D combination and the Dictation key on supported keyboards).

> If Dictation is enabled, those keys toggle Dictation normally (current

> behavior). If Dictation is disabled, those keys will enable the

> Dictation feature and show the network dialog if needed (new

> behavior).

>

> To do so, this change:

> 1. Adds a method called EnableOrToggleDictation(), which follows the

> behavior described above.

> 2. Adds automated tests at the AccessibilityController and

> AccessibilityManager levels.

> 3. Updates the accelerator action and associated methods to match the

> new method name.

> 4. Adds a feature flag so that the new behavior is protected behind

> the flag.

>

> Please see the UI mocks [1] for more details on desired behavior. Note

> that the mocks show updated dialog strings and two additional pieces

> of UI - those changes are left out of this change and will be added

> in a follow-up.

>

> [1] https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1mRnYcRpyzbY-EjzptCP3KRB5I7v_rM9Kl2zqhhQVZUY/edit#slide=id.p

entry.title: App Service: Reset app capabilities when Lacros disconnects
entry.content:
If Lacros disconnects, apps running in Lacros which are accessing

capabilities (e.g. camera) will no longer be running. Even if the Lacros

process restarts immediately, those apps may not restart, or may restart

without using the capability. Therefore, we should clear the capability

cache of any Lacros apps as soon as Lacros disconnects.

entry.title: chrome: don't return Browsers scheduled for deletion
entry.content:
This patch changes the majority of functions in browser_finder to

not return Browsers scheduled for deletion. This is because consumers

of these functions generally want a Browser they can make use of, but

a Browser scheduled for deletion should really not be used (you can't

add a WebContents to it).



In the long term, I think BrowserList really shouldn't contain

Browsers scheduled for deletion, but that's a much riskier change.

This is step in that direction.

entry.title: [css-flex] Don't mix auto minimum sizing and min-content contributions
entry.content:
Normally a flex item's automatic minimum size is smaller than its

min-content contribution. But replaced elements with a % max-width have

0px min-content contribution for ancient compat reasons as dictated by

https://drafts.csswg.org/css-sizing-3/#replaced-percentage-min-contribution



We had erroneously been applying automatic minimum size to a flex item's

min-content contribution during container intrinsic sizing, which blew

away the 0px min-content contribution.



Fixed: 1462398

entry.title: bindings: Make sync iterators more like IDL interfaces
entry.content:
SyncIterator.IRs were created right before processing IDL operation

groups (overload groups). Extended attributes' propagation, etc.

were not applied SyncIterator.IRs. However, upcoming AsyncIterator.IRs

need extended attributes' propagation, etc. and in general, it's good

to apply all compilation phases to IRs.



In order to improve the above point, make SyncIterator.IR more like

Interface.IR, e.g. inheriting IRMap.IR. Also apply all compilation

phases to SyncIterator.IRs.
